    <div align="center"><a href="http://www.defensivedriving.ca?REFID=11535 " target="_blank"><img src="online_training_images/safety-training-driving.jpg" alt="Safety training driving"/></a></div>
    <!-- TemplateBeginEditable name="mobilecontent" -->
    <blockquote>
      <p align="center">&nbsp;</p>
      <p align="center"><strong style="color: #063">SAFETY TRAINING OVERVIEW</strong></p>
      <p align="center"><img src="images/safety-training-logo.jpg"  alt="Safety Training"/></p>
      <p>BNR Online  Safety Training,  offers online safety courses to help you get certified in such courses as industrial overhead crane, low lift truck, fork truck operator's course etc. Are you seeking OSHA compliance certification? Our online training satisfies <strong style="color: #000">OSHA Standards, ANSI Standards, CSA Standards, MOL Guidelines and Regulations. Curriculum, which includes floor and aerial / scissor lift operation and safety, workplace hazards, OSHA compliance</strong></p>
      <p><br>
        Our certified online safety training courses sets us apart from  all the rest. Why you ask? They have been specially developed for those people  that may have difficulties reading and writing. We have put a great deal of  time in customizing these safety training programs for employees with  illiteracy. We have put our years of experience and expertise into developing  these simple and easy to use certified online programs.&nbsp;<br>
        <br>
        BNR caters to the small and corporate companies and  individuals as well, as long as they abide by our policies. Our online safety  training courses must have the evaluation form filled out (If Applicable) by a  certified person in order to be certified. You can fax it back to  1-866-735-0292.</p>
      <p><br>
        We will then put your card in your account. The evaluation forms  are in your account as well, along with your scores. If you don't have your  card within a couple of days after faxing your evaluation form please contact  us by using our support page. </p>
      <p><br>
        Most of our online OSHA and OHS safety training courses require an  evaluation to be completed on the trainee by a certified person. Except <a href="http://www.bnronlinewhmistraining.ca/" target="_blank">WHMIS</a>&nbsp;safety  training, pedestrian safety, lockout tagout and fall arrest. </p>
      <p><br>
        Pedestrian online safety training is designed to train your  employees to work safely around forklifts and other powered industrial trucks,  as well as a hand lift truck See (<a href="http://www.bnr-online-training.com/forklift_propane_crane_training.htm">Forklift  Training Questions</a>) This program will provide your employees with an  awareness of the hazards they can face in the workplace environment, and with  the tools for reducing the risk of an accident. You might want to read our  article on<a href="http://www.bnr-online-training.com/forklift-training.html">&nbsp;why forklift training</a>&nbsp;is required? </p>
      <p><span style="color: #060"><br>
        <strong>Why Take  Pedestrian Online Safety Training?</strong></span><br>
        <br>
        Trained pedestrians have an added benefit to industrial equipment  operators, enabling them to handle materials more safely and efficiently.  Pedestrian safety training is an important component in today's workplace and  is a needed asset in any company's comprehensive safety program </p>
      <p><br>
        Please don't hesitate to contact us if you have any questions,  concerns&nbsp;about&nbsp;our online  safety training courses.&nbsp;We'd like to thank some of our  customers in Calgary, Alberta, Edmonton,&nbsp;Winnipeg, Ottawa, Ontario,  Toronto, Hamilton, Oshawa, Vancouver, Nova Scotia and Saskatchewan. Not to  mention California, Texas, Arizona and other cities in the United States. </p>
    </blockquote>
